## Babylon azure acr pull

To test the new commands proceed as follow:
- install the new dependencies using `pip install -r requirements.txt`
- Add or edit the following lines in `config/platforms/platform.yaml`
```yaml
api_url: "https://dev.api.cosmotech.com"
api_scope: "http://dev.api.cosmotech.com/.default"
# ACR source registry name
acr_src_registry_name: "phoenixml.azurecr.io"
# ACR destination registry name
acr_dest_registry_name: "phoenixml.azurecr.io"
```
- Add or edit the following lines in `config/deployments/deploy.yml`
```yaml
# Simulator docker repository
simulator_repository: "hello-world"
# Simulator docker repository version
simulator_version: "latest"
```

### Commands

```bash
babylon azure acr pull -i this_image_does_not_exist
```
Should provide a clean error log
Please choose an existing image with `az acr repository list --name phoenixml --output table`
```bash
babylon azure acr pull -i existing_image:existing_tag
```
Should add a new entry to `docker image ls`
```bash
babylon azure acr pull
```
Should a new entry to `docker image ls` with the name specified in the `deploy.yaml` file

### Clean
Clean docker images using
```bash
docker image ls
docker image rm image_id
```